---
/**
 * WCD-27: Phosphorus.org — The Manifesto Front.
 *
 * Articulates the rejection of the "Attention Economy" and the
 * embrace of "Cognitive Sovereignty." Phosphorus as the Light Bringer,
 * backbone of ATP/DNA. Screen time as a cockpit for real-world agency.
 *
 * Imports the LivingVoid starfield concept and a central
 * Phosphorus Hero Atom description (R3F integration placeholder —
 * actual Three.js components require React island hydration in future WCD).
 */
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Phosphorus — The Light Bringer" description="Screen time is a cockpit, not a sinkhole. Cognitive sovereignty for the neurodivergent builder.">
  <main class="relative">

    <!-- ═══ THE VOID ═══ -->
    <!-- Starfield placeholder: in production, this becomes an R3F Canvas
         with LivingVoid + a central Phosphorus Hero Atom (WCD-18/19).
         For now, a CSS starfield approximation. -->
    <div class="fixed inset-0 -z-10 overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-p31-void" />
      <div
        class="absolute inset-0 opacity-30"
        style="background-image: radial-gradient(1px 1px at 20% 30%, rgba(255,255,255,0.8), transparent), radial-gradient(1px 1px at 40% 70%, rgba(255,255,255,0.6), transparent), radial-gradient(1px 1px at 60% 20%, rgba(255,255,255,0.7), transparent), radial-gradient(1px 1px at 80% 60%, rgba(255,255,255,0.5), transparent), radial-gradient(2px 2px at 15% 85%, rgba(139,124,201,0.88), transparent), radial-gradient(1px 1px at 70% 40%, rgba(255,255,255,0.4), transparent); background-size: 250px 250px;"
      />
    </div>

    <!-- ═══ HERO: THE LIGHT BRINGER ═══ -->
    <section class="relative min-h-screen flex flex-col items-center justify-center px-6 text-center">

      <!-- Phosphorus atom placeholder (future: R3F island) -->
      <div class="relative w-48 h-48 mb-12">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 rounded-full bg-lavender/5 animate-pulse" />
        <div class="absolute inset-4 rounded-full bg-lavender/10" />
        <div class="absolute inset-10 rounded-full bg-lavender/20" />
        <div class="absolute inset-16 rounded-full bg-lavender/40 shadow-[0_0_60px_rgba(139,124,201,0.35)]" />
        <div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center">
          <span class="text-5xl font-black text-lavender font-mono" style="text-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(139,124,201,0.45);">P</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-extrabold tracking-tight leading-none mb-6">
        <span class="text-p31-cloud">The Light</span>
        <br />
        <span class="text-lavender" style="text-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(139,124,201,0.28);">Bringer.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-p31-cloud-40 font-light max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Phosphorus. Element 15. The backbone of every ATP molecule
        that powers your cells and every strand of DNA that makes you, you.
      </p>

      <p class="text-sm text-p31-cloud-30 font-mono tracking-wider max-w-lg mx-auto">
        From the Greek <em class="text-p31-cloud-30">phōsphoros</em> — "bearer of light."
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ THE MANIFESTO ═══ -->
    <section class="relative px-6 py-32 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="space-y-16 text-lg text-p31-muted-50 leading-relaxed">

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-p31-cloud-90 mb-6">
            We Reject the Attention Economy.
          </h2>
          <p>
            The dominant paradigm treats your attention as a commodity to be extracted.
            Every notification, every infinite scroll, every autoplay video is a pickpocket
            reaching into the finite budget of your cognitive day.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            For neurodivergent minds — the ones running ADHD, autism, dyslexia, or any
            combination the DSM hasn't bothered to name yet — this extraction is not
            an inconvenience. It is an <span class="text-p31-cloud-80 font-semibold">existential threat</span>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-p31-cloud-90 mb-6">
            Screen Time Is a Cockpit.
          </h2>
          <p>
            A cockpit is not a sinkhole. A cockpit is where an operator sits to
            exercise agency over a system. The instruments exist to serve the pilot.
            The pilot does not exist to serve the instruments.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            Every tool we build at P31 Labs treats screen time as cockpit time.
            The screen is there to amplify your reach into the real world —
            to build molecules, to understand chemistry, to connect with another human
            who is also building. When the building is done, the screen should let you go.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-p31-cloud-90 mb-6">
            Cognitive Sovereignty.
          </h2>
          <p>
            Spoon theory is not a metaphor in our architecture. It is a
            <span class="font-mono text-lavender">first-class constraint</span>.
            Every interaction has a cognitive cost. Every reward loop has a
            measured half-life. Every session has a graceful exit.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            We do not optimize for "engagement." We optimize for
            <span class="text-p31-cloud-80 font-semibold">understanding</span>.
            A child who builds H₂O and feels the atoms snap together has learned more
            about covalent bonding in thirty seconds than a textbook teaches in thirty pages.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4">
            That is the mission. That is the light we carry.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- The Phosphorus Connection -->
        <div class="glass-panel p-8">
          <h3 class="font-mono text-sm text-lavender/60 uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4">
            Why Phosphorus?
          </h3>
          <p class="text-p31-cloud-40 leading-relaxed">
            Phosphorus is element 15 — a quiet backbone that makes loud things possible.
            It does not demand attention. It enables it. Every thought you've ever had
            was powered by adenosine <em>tri<span class="text-lavender">phosphate</span></em>.
            Every instruction in your genome is written on a
            <span class="text-lavender">phosphate</span> backbone.
          </p>
          <p class="text-p31-cloud-40 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            P31 — the only stable isotope of phosphorus — is our namesake because
            stability is not the absence of energy. It is energy that has found
            its structure. <span class="text-p31-muted font-semibold">Isostatically rigid.</span>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ THE SIGNAL ═══ -->
    <section class="px-6 py-24 text-center">
      <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto space-y-6">
        <p class="font-mono text-xs text-p31-cloud-30 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
          The Light Bringer · Element 15 · P31 Labs
        </p>
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-block glass-panel glass-panel-hover px-8 py-3 font-mono text-sm text-lavender/70 hover:text-lavender transition-colors"
        >
          Enter the Command Center
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <footer class="py-8 text-center border-t border-white/[0.04]">
    <p class="font-mono text-[10px] text-p31-cloud-30 tracking-wider">
      PHOSPHORUS.ORG · A P31 LABS MANIFESTO
    </p>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
